text.tspan: Which countries have managed to decouple agricultural output
Total factor productivity measures changes in the efficiency with which agricultural inputs are transformed into agricultural outputs.
If productivity did not improve, inputs would directly track outputs.
Data source: United States Department for Agriculture (USDA) Economic Research Service
